# sent_id = perry-291-s2
# text = Τῆς δ' ἐμπεσούσης εἰς φάραγγα κοιλώδη, Δέον βοηθεῖν, ὅδε ἀργὸς εἱστήκει, Τῷ δὲ Ἡρακλεῖ προσηύχετο μόνῳ Ἁπάντων θεῶν ὡς πολλὰ τιμωμένῳ.
# parallel_id = lyceum-aesop-p291/s2
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = When it fell into a deep ravine, needing help, he stood there idle; and he prayed only to Hercules of all the gods, as one much honored.
# literal_translation = Of it but having fallen into a ravine hollow, needing to help, he stood idle, to the but Hercules he prayed alone of all the gods as much honored.
