# sent_id = perry-291-s3
# text = Αὐτὸς δ' ἐπιστὰς εἶπε· Τῶν τρόχων ἅπτου Καὶ τοὺς βόας κέντριζε, τοῖς θεοῖς δ' εὔχου, Ὅταν τι ποιῇς καὐτὸς· μὴ μάτην εὔξῃ.
# parallel_id = lyceum-aesop-p291/s3
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = He himself, coming up, said: "Touch the wheels and prod the oxen, and pray to the gods, whenever you do something yourself; do not pray in vain."
# literal_translation = He himself but coming up said: Of the wheels touch! And the oxen prod, to the gods but pray, whenever something you do yourself; not in vain pray!
